The **Aztec diamond** $A_n$ of order $n$ is the union of unit squares in $\mathbb{Z}^2$ whose
centers $(x, y)$ satisfy $|x| + |y| \le n+1$ and $x + y \equiv n+1 \pmod{2}$. Equivalently,
$A_n$ is the region tiled by $2 \times 1$ dominoes in the celebrated theorem of
Elkies–Kuperberg–Larsen–Propp: the number of domino tilings of $A_n$ is

$$T(A_n) = 2^{\,n(n+1)/2}.$$

```figure caption="The Aztec diamond $A_3$ with one square at $(-1, 0)$ removed (punctured). Shading indicates the checkerboard coloring."
